HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 12
BY REPRESENTATIVE ZERINGUE
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Commends the American Shore and Beach Preservation
Association on the occasion of its one hundredth anniversary
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend the American Shore and Beach Preservation Association on the occasion of
3 its one hundredth anniversary.
4 WHEREAS, 2026 marks the centennial of the American Shore and Beach
5 Preservation Association (ASBPA), which works to advance a science-guided approach to
6 coastal restoration and protection; and
7 WHEREAS, ASBPA was founded in 1926 by visionary leaders who sought to
8 establish a forum "where the novice and he who has long wrestled with these problems can
9 seek more light; where the man of science and the statesman can exchange ideas and
10 collaborate together; where the idealist and lover of Nature and the economist can arrive at
11 a mutual understanding; where landscape artist and philanthropist can find an outlet for their
12 activities," thereby fostering collaboration and innovation for coastal stewardship; and
13 WHEREAS, the critical issues of shore and beach preservation, including the
14 promotion of community protection, a strong economy, ecological health, and recreation,
15 remain as vital today as they were at founding of ASBPA; and
16 WHEREAS, Louisiana's coastal communities and natural resources have benefitted
17 from ASBPA's efforts over the past century to translate coastal science and engineering,
18 guide policy, and advocate for resilient shores and beaches; and
19 WHEREAS, Louisiana aims to collaborate with ASBPA to build upon its century of
20 experience in coastal resilience and to advocate for solutions that adapt shore and beach
21 projects for future coastal challenges.
